-- Leicester Tigers Reach Ninth Consecutive Premiership Rugby Final
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2013-05-11T16:07:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-11/leicester-tigers-reach-ninth-consecutive-premiership-rugby-final.html
Leicester Tigers beat defending
champion Harlequins 33-16 to reach their ninth consecutive
English Premiership rugby final.  Niki Goneva, Niall Morris,  Tom Croft  and Mathew Tait
touched down as the Tigers oustscored Harlequins four tries to
one in the semifinal at Welford Road in Leicester. Toby Flood
kicked 13 points for Leicester, which led 13-9 at halftime.  Leicester will play Saracens or Northampton Saints in the
final May 25 at Twickenham Stadium in London. The Tigers will be
seeking their 10th English title.  Ross Chisolm scored a try and  Nick Evans  kicked 11 points
for Harlequins, which won both regular-season game against
Leicester.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
